# {{.Type}}: {{.Name}}

{{ .Description | trimspace }}

Service accounts are non-human identities used to authenticate automation (such as CI/CD pipelines) against the Kosli API. Use this resource to manage the lifecycle of a service account; manage its API keys with the `kosli_service_account_api_key` resource.

-> **Note:** Service accounts cannot be created in personal organizations. Only organization admins or the user that created the account may manage it.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/resources/kosli_service_account/resource.tf"}}

## Privileges

The `privilege` attribute must be one of the following:

- `admin` - Full administrative access
- `member` - Standard read/write access
- `snapshotter` - May report environment snapshots
- `reader` - Read-only access

You can only create a service account with a privilege equal to or lower than your own.

## Import

Service accounts can be imported using their name:

{{codefile "shell" "examples/resources/kosli_service_account/import.sh"}}

## Managing API Keys

To mint API keys for a service account, use the `kosli_service_account_api_key` resource. To look up an existing service account's metadata, use the `kosli_service_account` data source.

